The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Bangla curbs 

 Dhaka, May 11 (Reuters): Bangladeshs interim government has eased restrictions on former Prime Ministers Sheikh Hasina and Begum Khaleda Zia. 

 Leaders of Hasinas Awami League met her at home yesterday, while Khaleda was allowed to visit a relative. Security forces arrested a journalist, Tasneem Khalil, in Dhaka for criticism of the government. 

 US threat 

 Washington (Reuters): US and German officials said on Friday there was no new security threat in Germany after ABC News reported that terrorists were planning an attack on US military personnel in Germany. 

 Paris jail 

 Los Angeles (AP): Paris Hilton may spend far less than the 45 days she has been sentenced to serve in county jail. 




